WHEREAS, at one hundred years young, Mrs. Lewis finds joy in watching wildlife
in her backyard and, above all, cherishes spending time with her family, friends, and beloved
chihuahua, Lola; and
WHEREAS, her life exemplifies faith, love, resilience, and service, while leaving an
indelible mark on the community of Maringouin through her kindness, dedication, and
prosperous journey.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and congratulate Mrs. Elizabeth Kimball Lewis on the joyous
occasion of her one hundredth birthday and does honor her for an extraordinary life filled
with faith, enduring love, and meaningful contributions to her family, friends, and
community.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Mrs.
Elizabeth Kimball Lewis.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
